Chemical Engineer/Chemist

Joint Research and Development Inc

- Aberdeen, MD

JRAD is seeking a Chemical Engineer/Chemist for an immediate fill position located in Edgewood, MD.
Job Duties:
Serve as subject matter expert on test systems and fixtures used in a Government laboratory testing personal protective equipment (PPE) for protection against Chemical Weapons.
Maintain, troubleshoot and repair numerous complex laboratory test fixtures for testing filters, carbon and protective material permeability.
Disassemble laboratory test systems and reassemble as required in the laboratory.
Contribute to design and build of unique test systems to solve upcoming test challenges and needs.
Minimum Required Skills and Education:
Bachelor of Science in Chemical Engineering, or Bachelor of Science in Chemistry with experience in physical repair, design and build of mechanical systems.
Prior experience with maintaining, troubleshooting, designing and building laboratory test systems for testing PPE, or the demonstrated ability to learn this on the job.
Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.
Strong communication skills, both oral and written including proficiency in Microsoft Office products.
All experience levels will be considered, from junior to senior personnel.
Security Clearance
Must be able to obtain and maintain a DoD Secret clearance
